 353:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c **** /**
 354:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @ingroup tcp_raw
 355:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * Write data for sending (but does not send it immediately).
 356:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
 357:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * It waits in the expectation of more data being sent soon (as
 358:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * it can send them more efficiently by combining them together).
 359:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * To prompt the system to send data now, call tcp_output() after
 360:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * calling tcp_write().
 361:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
 362:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * This function enqueues the data pointed to by the argument dataptr. The length of
 363:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * the data is passed as the len parameter. The apiflags can be one or more of:
 364:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * - TCP_WRITE_FLAG_COPY: indicates whether the new memory should be allocated
 365:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *   for the data to be copied into. If this flag is not given, no new memory
 366:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *   should be allocated and the data should only be referenced by pointer. This
 367:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *   also means that the memory behind dataptr must not change until the data is
 368:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *   ACKed by the remote host
 369:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * - TCP_WRITE_FLAG_MORE: indicates that more data follows. If this is omitted,
 370:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *   the PSH flag is set in the last segment created by this call to tcp_write.
 371:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *   If this flag is given, the PSH flag is not set.
 372:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
 373:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * The tcp_write() function will fail and return ERR_MEM if the length
 374:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * of the data exceeds the current send buffer size or if the length of
 375:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * the queue of outgoing segment is larger than the upper limit defined
 376:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * in lwipopts.h. The number of bytes available in the output queue can
 377:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * be retrieved with the tcp_sndbuf() function.
 378:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
 379:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * The proper way to use this function is to call the function with at
 380:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * most tcp_sndbuf() bytes of data. If the function returns ERR_MEM,
 381:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * the application should wait until some of the currently enqueued
 382:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * data has been successfully received by the other host and try again.
 383:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
 384:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @param pcb Protocol control block for the TCP connection to enqueue data for.
 385:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @param arg Pointer to the data to be enqueued for sending.
 386:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @param len Data length in bytes
 387:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @param apiflags combination of following flags :
 388:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * - TCP_WRITE_FLAG_COPY (0x01) data will be copied into memory belonging to the stack
 389:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * - TCP_WRITE_FLAG_MORE (0x02) for TCP connection, PSH flag will not be set on last segment sent,
 390:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @return ERR_OK if enqueued, another err_t on error
 391:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  */
 392:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c **** err_t
 393:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c **** tcp_write(struct tcp_pcb *pcb, const void *arg, u16_t len, u8_t apiflags)
