2016:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c **** /**
2017:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * Send a TCP RESET packet (empty segment with RST flag set) to abort a
2018:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * connection.
2019:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
2020:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * Called by tcp_abort() (to abort a local connection), tcp_closen() (if not
2021:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * all data has been received by the application), tcp_timewait_input() (if a
2022:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * SYN is received) and tcp_process() (received segment in the wrong state).
2023:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
2024:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * Since a RST segment is in most cases not sent for an active connection,
2025:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * tcp_rst() has a number of arguments that are taken from a tcp_pcb for
2026:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * most other segment output functions.
2027:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
2028:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @param pcb TCP pcb (may be NULL if no pcb is available)
2029:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @param seqno the sequence number to use for the outgoing segment
2030:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @param ackno the acknowledge number to use for the outgoing segment
2031:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * @param local_ip the local IP address to send the segment from
