2049:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c **** /**
2050:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * Send a TCP RESET packet (empty segment with RST flag set) to show that there
2051:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * is no matching local connection for a received segment.
2052:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
2053:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * Called by tcp_input() (if no matching local pcb was found) and
2054:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * tcp_listen_input() (if incoming segment has ACK flag set).
2055:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  *
2056:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * Since a RST segment is in most cases not sent for an active connection,
2057:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * tcp_rst() has a number of arguments that are taken from a tcp_pcb for
2058:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/src/core/tcp_out.c ****  * most other segment output functions.
